Remove the .rule/.actor name-suffix holdover — rule-ness is aspect presence (#40)

Session 2026-07-19; full suite 277/277.

The `.rule`/`.actor` suffix in type NAMES was a holdover from before aspects
settled. A type IS a rule/actor by carrying a ruleAspect/actorAspect, never by a
name discriminator. `.actor` was already unused (actors are bare-named, detected
by actorAspect); this removes the remaining `.rule` suffix. No base-name
collisions exist in the corpus, so files rename straight to bare `.json` (no
merged-per-concept TypeDefinition needed).

Corpus (12 rule files, all git-mv'd .rule.json -> .json, typeName.name bared):
- draco.primes: AddNaturalSequence, PrimesFromNaturalSequence, RemoveCompositeNumbers.
- media domains: ConsumeReport, OriginateReport x {aerial, terrestrial, marine, ethereal}.
- test: org.nexonix.rules.rete.TupleFact.
- Domain elementTypeNames (Primes + 4 media, json + scala mirrors + Primes.drake)
  drop the `.rule` suffix on their rule entries.
- Generated rule .scala: loadRuleType(...) -> loadType(...); the Evrete
  `.newRule("<namePath>")` string loses its trailing `.rule` (object names and
  whereConditions references are unchanged — they were always base + "Rule").

Generator:
- Loaders: drop the aspect-suffix machinery — resourcePath/tryLoad lose the
  `aspect` param; loadRuleType / loadActorType / loadAll (unused) deleted; the
  emitter's ruleDefinitionLoad folds into typeDefinitionLoad (both emit loadType).
- stripAspect removed; all call sites now use the bare name directly.
- isRule = !RuleAspect.isEmpty(ruleAspect); isActor drops the `.actor` name clause;
  the actor emission branch drops its dead `.actor`->"Actor" nameSuffix (actors
  keep their bare name).
- actorKnowledge identifies a domain's rules by loading each elementTypeName member
  and testing ruleAspect presence, not by `.endsWith(".rule")`.
- drake header + parameterizedName/wildcardTypeName doc comments de-suffixed.

Tests & tooling:
- DracoGenTest / ExampleDomainsGenTest deriveScalaPath: rule-ness via ruleAspect
  (a rule emits `...Rule.scala`; plain types and actors keep the bare name — the
  dead `.actor`->`...Actor.scala` branch is gone). DrakeGenTest deriveDrakePath
  simplified to `stripSuffix(".json") + ".drake"`.
- Hardcoded `.rule.json` resource paths updated in PrimesRulesTest, TestValue,
  TupleFactReteTest, AerialGenTest.
- GeneratorCLI.elementCategory + the list-domain / list-domains / diff-type mods
  scripts categorize by aspect instead of the name suffix.

ExampleDomainsGenTest report-only map unchanged at 30 match / 18 differ. Closes #40.

